Columbus Avenue (buildings thereupon) east side, from West 65th to 66th Streets, showing the Ninth Avenue Elevated Line obstructing same from view. The open triangular area in the center is Lincoln Square, formed by the intersection of Broadway and Columbus Avenue above 65th Street. Note the "El" station at 66th Street.

No. 1: June, 1930 neg #44931
2&3: October 9, 1940

George L. Balgue

P. L. Sperr
